org.naomi.regex

Class BuiltInCharClass

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.naomi.regex.Pattern
      • org.naomi.regex.CharClass
        • org.naomi.regex.BuiltInCharClass
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    AlterationListener

    public class BuiltInCharClass
extends CharClass
    An instance of BuiltInCharClass is a Pattern which, on each repetition, matches any single character in the pre-defined set of characters denoted by its instantiating BuiltIn Enum constant. The internal "Not" flag in each instance can be set to make the class instead match all characters except those in the pre-defined set denoted by its instantiating BuiltIn Enum constant; this has the effect of matching the complement of the specified set of characters.

    A BuiltInCharClass can be instantiated with a constant from any of the enums: 

        CoreBuiltIn
    LocaleBuiltIn
    UniBlockBuiltIn
    UniScriptBuiltIn
